materials: Glue & Adhesives; Antifreeze; Brake Fluid; Degreasers; Fertilizer; Fungicides; Gasoline and Unwanted Fuels; Herbicides; Household Cleaners; Insecticides; Mercury Containing Items; Ni-Cd Batteries; Unused Paint; Paint Thinner; Pesticides; Photography Chemicals; Pool Chemicals; Batteries (Rechargeable); Solvents; Transmission Fluid; Used Motor Oil
notes: This site is located at the Plymouth Recycling Center on 56 Beech Hill Road in Plymouth, and is open to the residents of Ashland, Campton, Danbury, Dorchester, Easton, Ellsworth, Franconia, Groton, Landaff, Lisbon, Littleton, Lyman, Plymouth, Rumney, Sugar Hill, Thornton, Warren, Waterville Valley, and Wentworth.  This site will also allow a limited number of residents, from non-participating communities, to drop-off wastes during their collection for emergency situations only and with approval by the department.  Call the organizer prior to the collection date.  Up to ten gallons of liquid HHW materials or 100 pounds of dry HHW materials will be accepted from each resident.  This event will also accept craft and hobby supplies.
